# Built-in Google OAuth client for doce (optional).
#
# When both variables are set at BUILD time, doce bakes a built-in Google OAuth
# client into the binary, and the Connect flow lets users click "Continue with
# Google" without pasting their own Client ID / secret. If they're absent, the
# app still builds — users just supply their own OAuth client in the Connect
# form (the "bring your own" path).
#
# NOTE ON THE SECRET: for a desktop (installed) app, Google's client_secret is
# NOT confidential — it is a public identifier that ships inside every copy of
# the binary. PKCE (S256) is what actually protects the authorization flow. So
# embedding it here is expected and safe; it is not a credential leak.
#
# HOW IT'S INJECTED: `src-tauri/build.rs` reads these from the process env first
# (set them as CI build env vars for release builds), then falls back to this
# gitignored `.env` at the repo root for local dev. Copy this file to `.env`
# and fill in real values — `.env` is gitignored and must never be committed.

DOCE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=000000000000-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com
DOCE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=GOCSPX-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
